{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a believer."},{"time":2000,"text":"I'm a believer in global warming,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and my record is good"},{"time":6000,"text":"on the subject."},{"time":8000,"text":"But my subject"},{"time":10000,"text":"is national security."},{"time":12000,"text":"We have to get off of oil purchased"},{"time":15000,"text":"from the enemy."},{"time":17000,"text":"I'm talking about OPEC oil."},{"time":19000,"text":"And let me take you back"},{"time":21000,"text":"100 years"},{"time":23000,"text":"to 1912."},{"time":26000,"text":"You're probably thinking that was my birth year."},{"time":29000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":31000,"text":"It wasn't. It was 1928."},{"time":34000,"text":"But go back to 1912,"},{"time":36000,"text":"100 years ago,"},{"time":38000,"text":"and look at that point"},{"time":40000,"text":"what we, our country, was faced with."},{"time":43000,"text":"It's the same energy question"},{"time":45000,"text":"that you're looking at today,"},{"time":47000,"text":"but it's different sources of fuel."},{"time":50000,"text":"A hundred years ago"},{"time":52000,"text":"we were looking at coal, of course,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and we were looking at whale oil"},{"time":56000,"text":"and we were looking at crude oil."},{"time":59000,"text":"At that point,"},{"time":61000,"text":"we were looking for a fuel"},{"time":63000,"text":"that was cleaner,"},{"time":65000,"text":"it was cheaper,"},{"time":67000,"text":"and it wasn't ours though,"},{"time":70000,"text":"it was theirs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"So at that point, 1912,"},{"time":75000,"text":"we selected crude oil over whale oil"},{"time":78000,"text":"and some more coal."},{"time":81000,"text":"But as we moved on"},{"time":83000,"text":"to the period now, 100 years later,"},{"time":86000,"text":"we're back really"},{"time":88000,"text":"at another decision point."},{"time":90000,"text":"What is the decision point?"},{"time":92000,"text":"It's what we're going to use"},{"time":94000,"text":"in the future."},{"time":96000,"text":"So from here,"},{"time":98000,"text":"it's pretty clear to me,"},{"time":100000,"text":"we would prefer to have"},{"time":102000,"text":"cleaner, cheaper,"},{"time":104000,"text":"domestic, ours --"},{"time":107000,"text":"and we have that, we have that --"},{"time":110000,"text":"which is natural gas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"So here you are,"},{"time":114000,"text":"that the cost of all this to the world"},{"time":118000,"text":"is 89 million barrels of oil,"},{"time":121000,"text":"give or take a few barrels, every day."},{"time":123000,"text":"And the cost annually"},{"time":125000,"text":"is three trillion dollars."},{"time":128000,"text":"And one trillion of that"},{"time":130000,"text":"goes to OPEC."},{"time":132000,"text":"That has got to be stopped."},{"time":135000,"text":"Now if you look at the cost of OPEC,"},{"time":138000,"text":"it cost seven trillion dollars --"},{"time":141000,"text":"on the Milken Institute study last year --"},{"time":143000,"text":"seven trillion dollars"},{"time":145000,"text":"since 1976,"},{"time":147000,"text":"is what we paid for oil from OPEC."},{"time":150000,"text":"Now that includes the cost of military"},{"time":152000,"text":"and the cost of the fuel both."},{"time":155000,"text":"But it's the greatest transfer of wealth,"},{"time":160000,"text":"from one group to another"},{"time":162000,"text":"in the history of mankind."},{"time":164000,"text":"And it continues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"Now when you look"},{"time":168000,"text":"at where is the transfer of wealth,"},{"time":170000,"text":"you can see here"},{"time":172000,"text":"that we have the arrows"},{"time":175000,"text":"going into the Mid-East"},{"time":177000,"text":"and away from us."},{"time":179000,"text":"And with that,"},{"time":181000,"text":"we have found ourselves"},{"time":183000,"text":"to be the world's policemen."},{"time":185000,"text":"We are policing the world,"},{"time":187000,"text":"and how are we doing that?"},{"time":190000,"text":"I know the response to this."},{"time":194000,"text":"I would bet there aren't 10 percent of you in the room"},{"time":198000,"text":"that know how many aircraft carriers there are in the world."},{"time":203000,"text":"Raise your hand if you think you know."},{"time":206000,"text":"There are 12."},{"time":208000,"text":"One is under construction by the Chinese"},{"time":210000,"text":"and the other 11 belong to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"Why do we have 11 aircraft carriers?"},{"time":217000,"text":"Do we have a corner on the market?"},{"time":220000,"text":"Are we smarter than anybody else? I'm not sure."},{"time":223000,"text":"If you look at where they're located --"},{"time":225000,"text":"and on this slide it's the red blobs on there --"},{"time":228000,"text":"there are five that are operating in the Mid-East,"},{"time":232000,"text":"and the rest of them are in the United States."},{"time":235000,"text":"They just move back to the Mid-East and those come back."},{"time":238000,"text":"So actually most of the 11 we have"},{"time":241000,"text":"are tied up in the Mid-East."},{"time":244000,"text":"Why? Why are they in the Mid-East?"},{"time":247000,"text":"They're there to control,"},{"time":249000,"text":"keep the shipping lanes open"},{"time":251000,"text":"and make oil available."},{"time":253000,"text":"And the United States uses about 20 million barrels a day,"},{"time":257000,"text":"which is about 25 percent of all the oil used"},{"time":261000,"text":"everyday in the world."},{"time":264000,"text":"And we're doing it with four percent of the population."},{"time":267000,"text":"Somehow that doesn't seem right."},{"time":270000,"text":"That's not sustainable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"So where do we go from here?"},{"time":274000,"text":"Does that continue?"},{"time":276000,"text":"Yes, it's going to continue."},{"time":278000,"text":"The slide you're looking at here"},{"time":280000,"text":"is 1990 to 2040."},{"time":282000,"text":"Over that period"},{"time":284000,"text":"you are going to double your demand."},{"time":287000,"text":"And when you look at what we're using the oil for,"},{"time":290000,"text":"70 percent of it"},{"time":292000,"text":"is used for transportation fuel."},{"time":294000,"text":"So when somebody says,"},{"time":296000,"text":"\"Let's go more nuclear,"},{"time":298000,"text":"let's go wind, let's go solar,\""},{"time":301000,"text":"fine; I'm for anything American,"},{"time":304000,"text":"anything American."},{"time":306000,"text":"But if you're going to do anything"},{"time":308000,"text":"about the dependency on foreign oil,"},{"time":311000,"text":"you have to address transportation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"So here we are"},{"time":315000,"text":"using 20 million barrels a day --"},{"time":318000,"text":"producing eight, importing 12,"},{"time":321000,"text":"and from the 12,"},{"time":323000,"text":"five comes from OPEC."},{"time":328000,"text":"When you look at the biggest user and the second largest user,"},{"time":331000,"text":"we use 20 million barrels"},{"time":333000,"text":"and the Chinese use 10."},{"time":335000,"text":"The Chinese have a little bit better plan --"},{"time":339000,"text":"or they have a plan;"},{"time":341000,"text":"we have no plan."},{"time":343000,"text":"In the history of America,"},{"time":345000,"text":"we've never had an energy plan."},{"time":347000,"text":"We don't even realize the resources"},{"time":349000,"text":"that we have available to us."},{"time":351000,"text":"If you take the last 10 years"},{"time":353000,"text":"and bring forward,"},{"time":355000,"text":"you've transferred to OPEC a trillion dollars."},{"time":359000,"text":"If you go forward the next 10 years"},{"time":362000,"text":"and cap the price of oil at 100 dollars a barrel,"},{"time":365000,"text":"you will pay 2.2 trillion."},{"time":368000,"text":"That's not sustainable either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370000,"text":"But the days of cheap oil are over."},{"time":373000,"text":"They're over."},{"time":375000,"text":"They make it very clear to you,"},{"time":378000,"text":"the Saudis do,"},{"time":381000,"text":"they have to have 94 dollars a barrel"},{"time":384000,"text":"to make their social commitments."},{"time":386000,"text":"Now I had people in Washington last week told me,"},{"time":390000,"text":"he said, \"The Saudis can produce the oil"},{"time":393000,"text":"for five dollars a barrel."},{"time":395000,"text":"That has nothing to do with it."},{"time":397000,"text":"It's what they have to pay for"},{"time":399000,"text":"is what we are going to pay for oil.\""},{"time":401000,"text":"There is no free market for oil."},{"time":403000,"text":"The oil is priced off the margin."},{"time":405000,"text":"And the OPEC nations"},{"time":408000,"text":"are the ones that price the oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"So where are we headed from here?"},{"time":413000,"text":"We're headed to natural gas."},{"time":416000,"text":"Natural gas will do everything"},{"time":418000,"text":"we want it to do."},{"time":420000,"text":"It's 130 octane fuel."},{"time":423000,"text":"It's 25 percent cleaner than oil."},{"time":426000,"text":"It's ours, we have an abundance of it."},{"time":429000,"text":"And it does not require a refinery."},{"time":432000,"text":"It comes out of the ground at 130 octane."},{"time":434000,"text":"Run it through the separator and you're ready to use it."},{"time":437000,"text":"It's going to be very simple for us to use."},{"time":440000,"text":"It's going to be simple to accomplish this."},{"time":442000,"text":"You're going to find, and I'll tell you in just a minute,"},{"time":444000,"text":"what you're looking for to make it happen."},{"time":447000,"text":"But here you can look at the list."},{"time":450000,"text":"Natural gas will fit all of those."},{"time":453000,"text":"It will replace or be able to be used for that."},{"time":457000,"text":"It's for power generation, transportation,"},{"time":459000,"text":"it's peaking fuel, it's all those."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462000,"text":"Do we have enough natural gas?"},{"time":465000,"text":"Look at the bar on the left. It's 24 trillion."},{"time":468000,"text":"It's what we use a year."},{"time":470000,"text":"Go forward"},{"time":472000,"text":"and the estimates that you have"},{"time":474000,"text":"from the EIA and onto the industry estimates --"},{"time":478000,"text":"the industry knows what they're talking about --"},{"time":480000,"text":"we've got 4,000 trillion cubic feet"},{"time":483000,"text":"of natural gas that's available to us."},{"time":485000,"text":"How does that translate"},{"time":487000,"text":"to barrels of oil equivalent?"},{"time":489000,"text":"It would be three times"},{"time":491000,"text":"what the Saudis claim they have."},{"time":493000,"text":"And they claim they have 250 billion barrels of oil,"},{"time":496000,"text":"which I do not believe."},{"time":498000,"text":"I think it's probably 175 billion barrels."},{"time":503000,"text":"But anyway, whether they say they're right or whatever,"},{"time":506000,"text":"we have plenty of natural gas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"So I have tried to target"},{"time":510000,"text":"on where we use the natural gas."},{"time":512000,"text":"And where I've targeted"},{"time":514000,"text":"is on the heavy-duty trucks."},{"time":516000,"text":"There are eight million of them."},{"time":518000,"text":"You take eight million trucks --"},{"time":520000,"text":"these are 18-wheelers --"},{"time":522000,"text":"and take them to natural gas,"},{"time":524000,"text":"reduce carbon by 30 percent,"},{"time":527000,"text":"it is cheaper"},{"time":529000,"text":"and it will cut our imports"},{"time":532000,"text":"three million barrels."},{"time":534000,"text":"So you will cut 60 percent off of OPEC"},{"time":537000,"text":"with eight million trucks."},{"time":539000,"text":"There are 250 million vehicles in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542000,"text":"So what you have"},{"time":544000,"text":"is natural gas is the bridge fuel,"},{"time":547000,"text":"is the way I see it."},{"time":549000,"text":"I don't have to worry"},{"time":551000,"text":"about the bridge to where at my age."},{"time":554000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":556000,"text":"That's your concern."},{"time":559000,"text":"But when you look at the natural gas we have"},{"time":561000,"text":"it could very well be"},{"time":563000,"text":"the bridge to natural gas,"},{"time":565000,"text":"because you have plenty of natural gas."},{"time":568000,"text":"But as I said, I'm for anything American."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"Now let me take you -- I've been a realist --"},{"time":574000,"text":"I went from theorist early to realist."},{"time":576000,"text":"I'm back to theorist again."},{"time":578000,"text":"If you look at the world,"},{"time":581000,"text":"you have methane hydrates in the ocean"},{"time":584000,"text":"around every continent."},{"time":586000,"text":"And here you can see methane,"},{"time":589000,"text":"if that's the way you're going to go,"},{"time":591000,"text":"that there's plenty of methane --"},{"time":593000,"text":"natural gas is methane,"},{"time":595000,"text":"methane and natural gas are interchangeable --"},{"time":597000,"text":"but if you decide"},{"time":599000,"text":"that you're going to use some methane --"},{"time":601000,"text":"and I'm gone, so it's up to you --"},{"time":603000,"text":"but we do have"},{"time":605000,"text":"plenty of methane hydrates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608000,"text":"So I think I've made my point"},{"time":611000,"text":"that we have to get on our own resources in America."},{"time":616000,"text":"If we do --"},{"time":619000,"text":"it's costing us a billion dollars a day for oil."},{"time":622000,"text":"And yet, we have no energy plan."},{"time":625000,"text":"So there's nothing going on"},{"time":628000,"text":"that impresses me"},{"time":631000,"text":"in Washington on that plan,"},{"time":634000,"text":"other than I'm trying to focus"},{"time":636000,"text":"on that eight million 18-wheelers."},{"time":639000,"text":"If we could do that,"},{"time":641000,"text":"I think we would take our first step"},{"time":643000,"text":"to an energy plan."},{"time":645000,"text":"If we did, we could see"},{"time":647000,"text":"that our own resources are easier to use"},{"time":650000,"text":"than anybody can imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thanks for that."},{"time":664000,"text":"So from your point of view,"},{"time":666000,"text":"you had this great Pickens Plan"},{"time":668000,"text":"that was based on wind energy,"},{"time":671000,"text":"and you abandoned it basically"},{"time":673000,"text":"because the economics changed."},{"time":675000,"text":"What happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":677000,"text":"TBP: I lost 150 million dollars."},{"time":679000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":681000,"text":"That'll make you abandon something."},{"time":684000,"text":"No, what happened to us, Chris,"},{"time":687000,"text":"is that power, it's priced off the margin."},{"time":693000,"text":"And so the margin is natural gas."},{"time":696000,"text":"And at the time I went into the wind business,"},{"time":698000,"text":"natural gas was nine dollars."},{"time":700000,"text":"Today it's two dollars and forty cents."},{"time":703000,"text":"You cannot do a wind deal"},{"time":705000,"text":"under six dollars an MCF."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"CA: So what happened was"},{"time":709000,"text":"that, through increased ability"},{"time":713000,"text":"to use fracking technology,"},{"time":715000,"text":"the calculated reserves of natural gas kind of exploded"},{"time":718000,"text":"and the price plummeted,"},{"time":721000,"text":"which made wind uncompetitive."},{"time":723000,"text":"In a nutshell that's what happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"TBP: That's what happened."},{"time":727000,"text":"We found out that we could go to the source rock,"},{"time":729000,"text":"which were the carboniferous shales in the basins."},{"time":732000,"text":"The first one was Barnett Shale in Texas"},{"time":735000,"text":"and then the Marcellus up in the Northeast"},{"time":738000,"text":"across New York, Pennsylvania, West Virginia;"},{"time":741000,"text":"and Haynesville in Louisiana."},{"time":743000,"text":"This stuff is everywhere."},{"time":745000,"text":"We are overwhelmed with natural gas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"CA: And now you're a big investor in that and bringing that to market?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":751000,"text":"TBP: Well you say a big investor."},{"time":753000,"text":"It's my life."},{"time":755000,"text":"I'm a geologist, got out of school in '51,"},{"time":757000,"text":"and I've been in the industry my entire life."},{"time":759000,"text":"Now I do own stocks."},{"time":762000,"text":"I'm not a big natural gas producer."},{"time":765000,"text":"Somebody the other day said"},{"time":767000,"text":"I was the second largest natural gas producer in the United States."},{"time":769000,"text":"Don't I wish."},{"time":771000,"text":"But no, I'm not. I own stocks."},{"time":774000,"text":"But I also am in the fueling business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777000,"text":"CA: But natural gas is a fossil fuel."},{"time":780000,"text":"You burn it,"},{"time":782000,"text":"you release CO2."},{"time":784000,"text":"So you believe in the threat of climate change."},{"time":788000,"text":"Why doesn't that prospect"},{"time":790000,"text":"concern you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"TBP: Well you're going to have to use something."},{"time":795000,"text":"What do you have to replace it?"},{"time":799000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":804000,"text":"CA: No, no. The argument that it's a bridge fuel makes sense,"},{"time":807000,"text":"because the amount of CO2 per unit of energy"},{"time":811000,"text":"is lower than oil and coal, correct?"},{"time":814000,"text":"And so everyone can be at least happy"},{"time":817000,"text":"to see a shift from coal or oil to natural gas."},{"time":820000,"text":"But if that's it"},{"time":822000,"text":"and that becomes the reason"},{"time":824000,"text":"that renewables don't get invested in,"},{"time":827000,"text":"then, long-term, we're screwed anyway, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"TBP: Well I'm not ready to give up,"},{"time":832000,"text":"but Jim and I talked"},{"time":834000,"text":"there as he left,"},{"time":836000,"text":"and I said, \"How do you feel about natural gas?\""},{"time":838000,"text":"And he said, \"Well it's a bridge fuel, is what it is.\""},{"time":841000,"text":"And I said, \"Bridge to what?"},{"time":843000,"text":"Where are we headed?\""},{"time":845000,"text":"See but again, I told you, I don't have to worry with that."},{"time":847000,"text":"You all do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"CA: But I don't think that's right, Boone."},{"time":851000,"text":"I think you're a person who believes in your legacy."},{"time":854000,"text":"You've made the money you need."},{"time":856000,"text":"You're one of the few people in a position"},{"time":859000,"text":"to really swing the debate."},{"time":862000,"text":"Do you support the idea of some kind of price on carbon?"},{"time":865000,"text":"Does that make sense?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"TBP: I don't like that"},{"time":869000,"text":"because it ends up the government is going to run the program."},{"time":872000,"text":"I can tell you it will be a failure."},{"time":874000,"text":"The government is not successful"},{"time":877000,"text":"on these things."},{"time":879000,"text":"They just aren't, it's a bad deal."},{"time":882000,"text":"Look at Solyndra, or whatever it was."},{"time":885000,"text":"I mean, that was told to be a bad idea 10 times,"},{"time":887000,"text":"they went ahead and did it anyway."},{"time":889000,"text":"But that only blew out 500 million."},{"time":892000,"text":"I think it's closer to a billion."},{"time":895000,"text":"But Chris, I think where we're headed,"},{"time":898000,"text":"the long-term,"},{"time":901000,"text":"I don't mind going back to nuclear."},{"time":903000,"text":"And I can tell you what the last page"},{"time":905000,"text":"of the report that will take them five years to write"},{"time":907000,"text":"will be."},{"time":909000,"text":"One, don't build a reformer on a fault."},{"time":912000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":914000,"text":"And number two,"},{"time":916000,"text":"do not build a reformer on the ocean."},{"time":919000,"text":"And now I think reformers are safe."},{"time":922000,"text":"Move them inland"},{"time":924000,"text":"and on very stable ground"},{"time":928000,"text":"and build the reformers."},{"time":930000,"text":"There isn't anything wrong with nuke."},{"time":932000,"text":"You're going to have to have energy. There is no question."},{"time":934000,"text":"You can't -- okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936000,"text":"CA: One of the questions from the audience"},{"time":939000,"text":"is, with fracking and the natural gas process,"},{"time":942000,"text":"what about the problem of methane leaking from that,"},{"time":945000,"text":"methane being a worse global warming gas"},{"time":947000,"text":"than CO2?"},{"time":949000,"text":"Is that a concern?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":951000,"text":"TBP: Fracking? What is fracking?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":953000,"text":"CA: Fracking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":956000,"text":"TBP: I'm teasing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":960000,"text":"CA: We've got a little bit of accent incompatibility here, you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"TBP: No, let me tell you,"},{"time":966000,"text":"I've told you what my age was."},{"time":968000,"text":"I got out of school in '51."},{"time":970000,"text":"I witnessed my first frack job"},{"time":972000,"text":"at border Texas in 1953."},{"time":974000,"text":"Fracking came out in '47,"},{"time":976000,"text":"and don't believe for a minute"},{"time":978000,"text":"when our president gets up there"},{"time":980000,"text":"and says the Department of Energy 30 years ago"},{"time":983000,"text":"developed fracking."},{"time":985000,"text":"I don't know what in the hell he's talking about."},{"time":988000,"text":"I mean seriously, the Department of Energy"},{"time":990000,"text":"did not have anything to do with fracking."},{"time":993000,"text":"The first frack job was in '47."},{"time":995000,"text":"I saw my first one in '53."},{"time":998000,"text":"I've fracked over 3,000 wells in my life."},{"time":1001000,"text":"Never had a problem"},{"time":1003000,"text":"with messing up an aquifer or anything else."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Now the largest aquifer in North America"},{"time":1008000,"text":"is from Midland, Texas to the South Dakota border,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"across eight states --"},{"time":1013000,"text":"big aquifer:"},{"time":1015000,"text":"Ogallala, Triassic age."},{"time":1018000,"text":"There had to have been 800,000 wells fracked"},{"time":1021000,"text":"in Oklahoma, Texas, Kansas"},{"time":1024000,"text":"in that aquifer."},{"time":1026000,"text":"There's no problems."},{"time":1028000,"text":"I don't understand why"},{"time":1030000,"text":"the media is focused on Eastern Pennsylvania."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034000,"text":"CA: All right, so you don't support a carbon tax of any kind"},{"time":1037000,"text":"or a price on carbon."},{"time":1039000,"text":"Your picture then I guess"},{"time":1042000,"text":"of how the world eventually gets off fossil fuels"},{"time":1044000,"text":"is through innovation ultimately,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"that we'll someday make solar and nuclear cost competitive?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052000,"text":"TBP: Solar and wind, Jim and I agreed on that in 13 seconds."},{"time":1056000,"text":"That is, it's going to be a small part,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"because you can't rely on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060000,"text":"CA: So how does the world get off fossil fuels?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062000,"text":"TBP: How do we get there?"},{"time":1064000,"text":"We have so much natural gas,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"a day will not come"},{"time":1068000,"text":"where you say, \"Well let's don't use that anymore.\""},{"time":1070000,"text":"You'll keep using it. It is the cleanest of all."},{"time":1073000,"text":"And if you look at California,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"they use 2,500 buses."},{"time":1077000,"text":"LAMTA have been on natural gas"},{"time":1081000,"text":"for 25 years."},{"time":1083000,"text":"The Ft. Worth T"},{"time":1085000,"text":"has been on it for 25 years."},{"time":1087000,"text":"Why? Air quality was the reason they used natural gas"},{"time":1090000,"text":"and got away from diesel."},{"time":1092000,"text":"Why are all the trash trucks today in Southern California"},{"time":1094000,"text":"on natural gas?"},{"time":1096000,"text":"It's because of air quality."},{"time":1098000,"text":"I know what you're telling me, and I'm not disagreeing with you."},{"time":1101000,"text":"How in the hell can we get off the natural gas at some point?"},{"time":1104000,"text":"And I say, that is your problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109000,"text":"CA: All right,"},{"time":1111000,"text":"so it's the bridge fuel."},{"time":1113000,"text":"What is at the other end of that bridge"},{"time":1115000,"text":"is for this audience to figure out."},{"time":1117000,"text":"If someone comes to you with a plan"},{"time":1119000,"text":"that really looks like it might be part of this solution,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"are you ready to invest in those technologies,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"even if they aren't maximized for profits,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"they might be maximized for the future health of the planet?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1129000,"text":"TBP: I lost 150 million on the wind, okay."},{"time":1132000,"text":"Yeah, sure, I'm game for it."},{"time":1135000,"text":"Because, again,"},{"time":1138000,"text":"I'm trying to get energy solved for America."},{"time":1142000,"text":"And anything American"},{"time":1145000,"text":"will work for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1147000,"text":"CA: Boone, I really, really appreciate you coming here,"},{"time":1149000,"text":"engaging in this conversation."},{"time":1151000,"text":"I think there's a lot of people who will want to engage with you."},{"time":1154000,"text":"And that was a real gift you gave this audience."},{"time":1156000,"text":"Thank you so much. (TBP: You bet, Chris. Thank you.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1159000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}